  <h3>Q: Myth or Fact? Concrete docks are more expensive than wooden docks.</h3>
  <p>
    A: The Facts:
    <ul>
      <li>Concrete docks’ lifespan is more than two times that of a wooden dock</li>
      <li>Less yearly maintenance than wood dock</li>
      <li>Positive floatation + large mass = stability & usable surface area over life</li>
      <li>Appearance holds over time (more than wooden dock)</li>
    </ul>
  </p><br>

