  <h3>Q: Why is pressure treated wood (CCA) not a good choice for docks?</h3>
  <p>
    A: Pressure-treated wood uses chromated copper arsenate (CCA) as a preservative.  CCA has been linked to cancer and to environmental damage in lakes where it has been used.  For further information, check out the website for No CCA Wood: <%= link_to 'http://www.noccawood.ca/links.htm', 'http://www.noccawood.ca/links.htm' %>.  It goes through a variety of the problems associated with CCA treated wood.
  </p>

  <div class="clearfix"></div>

